MoonLightKernel for Xiaomi Redmi 12 (fire/heat)
=================================================

This tree builds the MediaTek arm64 kernel for Xiaomi Redmi 12 variants and
packages the result as an AnyKernel3 flashable ZIP.

Maintainers are listed in ``AUTHORS``: 1VicTim1 and Flasix67.  The project
retains the original repository history and existing contributor attribution.

Build
-----

Dependencies on the host are ``bash``, ``make``, ``curl``, ``tar``, ``git``,
``zip`` and ``ccache``.  The build script downloads the pinned Android
``clang-r383902b`` toolchain from AOSP into the user cache on first use, and
keeps compiler objects in the ccache directory for faster rebuilds.

::

    ./build.sh fire
    ./build.sh heat

The default target is ``fire``.  Output kernel objects are written below
``out/<device>/`` and the flashable archive is written to ``dist/``.
AnyKernel3 is fetched from the upstream ``osm0sis/AnyKernel3`` repository at a
pinned revision and configured for the ``fire``/``heat`` device names, boot
partition auto-slot detection and ramdisk preservation.

Useful overrides
----------------

::

    JOBS=8 ./build.sh fire
    TOOLCHAIN_DIR=/path/to/clang-r383902b ./build.sh fire
    CCACHE_DIR=/path/to/ccache CCACHE_MAXSIZE=20G ./build.sh heat
    ./build.sh fire clean

Kernel configuration
--------------------

The production ``fire_defconfig`` retains the existing performance-oriented
ThinLTO and scheduler settings.  It also enables relative kallsyms addresses
to reduce symbol-table memory use while preserving kernel symbol lookup, and
enables Android schedtune cgroups required by the userspace ``/dev/stune``
policy assignments.
